                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Iddings</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 332.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt on
                    February 11 of your telegraphic instruction of February 10. The ambassador being
                    absent, I immediately called upon the minister for foreign affairs, Signor
                    Tittoni, and informed him of your suggestions. The minister said he approved
                    heartily of all that the United States proposed—that the neutral powers should
                    use their good offices to persuade Japan and Russia to respect the neutrality of
                    China, and that it would be desirable to localize and limit the area of
                    hostilities as far as possible, so as to avoid disturbance among the Chinese
                    populations. As to sending instructions in this sense to Italian representatives
                    in Petersburg, Tokyo, and Peking, he would give a definite reply as soon as he
                    had heard the views of the cabinets in Berlin, London, and Paris.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis Morris Iddings.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
